<br>
I've gotten schmucked more times than I can count with charm so far, but I'm still having a blast with it. If I'm really bored and willing to chance a death for some quick xp, I charm a pet, BO5 it, then sick it on one mob at a time until it's near dead (usually within a few minutes, since I don't bother backing it off for enrage). When it gets into a fight its clearly going to lose, I gate. Once you're gone, the mobs should continue to duke it out and the elemental will die (wouldn't want to leave a BO5'd elemental up to kill everyone else that happens along). I can usually get 2 or 3 mobs down if charm doesn't break early, and make around 13-20% of an AA. Once you've gated, a few minutes of medding and you're back in the fray. The biggest problem is finding a spot to safely charm a pet and pull. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3284">Sarelorn Stonecaller</a><BR>
